        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @Quest- Who is better? The only other keeper in world football who has a realistic claim to be #1 is David De Gea which is why Real covet him so much. Purely on shot-stopping ability, Neuer is THE best in the world. He doesn't command his area like a Seaman/Schmeichel/Buffon at their peak but that also has to do with the fact Bayern don't have good CBs like those 3 did/do have. I haven't seen many keepers look confident when they have poor defenders in front of them. Ultimately when you make a list of the things you want in a keeper, Neuer will tick more boxes than any other. Making world-class saves out of nowhere is often the biggest indicator of a top keeper. Most struggle instantly switching on when their team is heavily dominating but Neuer doesn't. He made 2 or 3 saves at the Emirates that no other keeper would make, in a game when they were under pressure like they haven't been since the Barcelona game last season. No keeper has a winning % in 1-on-1s.
